Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} lengthways into 1cm slices, then chop into 1cm wide
chips (no need to peel).

Pop the chips onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{}, sprinkle over the
@dried rosemary{2%tsp}, season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{} and toss to coat.
Spread out in a single layer.

> TIP: Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, bake on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-30%minutes}.
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, drain the @halloumi{225%g}, then cut widthways into 2 slices per
person. Place them into a #small bowl{} of cold water and leave to soak.

Remove the stems from the @portobello mushrooms{2} (but leave the mushrooms
whole).

Heat a drizzle of @oil{} in a large #frying pan{} on high heat. Fry the
mushrooms until golden brown, ~{4-5%minutes}, then turn over and cook for a
further ~{4-5%minutes}. Adjust the heat if necessary.

While the mushrooms fry, peel and grate the @garlic{2%cloves}(peeled) (or use a
#garlic press{}). Cut the @medium tomato{1} into 2cm chunks.

In a #medium bowl{}, combine the @balsamic vinegar{12%ml} and
@olive oil{1%tbsp}(for the dressing). Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{}.
Mix the tomatoes into the dressing and set aside.

For the final min of mushroom frying time, reduce the heat to medium, then add
the garlic and @butter{20%g} to the pan and spoon it over the mushrooms to
coat them.

Once cooked, transfer the mushrooms, stem-side up, to a baking tray.

When the chips have about 10 mins left, remove them from the oven, sprinkle
over the @grated hard Italian style cheese{20%g} and return to the top shelf.

Pop the mushrooms on the middle shelf and bake until the mushrooms are fully
cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

Meanwhile, wipe your frying pan clean with kitchen paper to remove any leftover
garlic.

Remove the halloumi slices from the cold water, pop them onto a #plate{} lined
with #kitchen paper{} and pat them dry.

Return the (now empty) pan to medium-high heat and drizzle with oil. Once hot,
add the halloumi and fry until golden, ~{2-3%minutes} each side.

Add the @red pepper chilli jelly{37%g} to the pan. Turn the halloumi slices to
coat them evenly in the sticky glaze.

Just before everything's ready, halve the @burger buns{2}. Pop them into the
oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

When everything's ready, spread the @fresh pesto{32%g} over the bun bases and
lids. Top the bases with the glazed halloumi, the garlic butter mushrooms and
some of the @wild rocket{20%g}, then sandwich shut with the bun lids.

Toss the remaining rocket with the tomato and dressing.

Serve your craft burgers with the rocket salad and cheesy chips alongside.
Add some @mayonnaise{2%tbsp} on the side for dipping.

Enjoy!